				<cite class="fn">VAC</cite> 				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.hangthebankers.com/13-most-underreported-news-stories-of-2013/#comment-20166">	January 13, 2014 at 1:06 pm</a></div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>How about protests in Catalonia in favour of a referendum on independence from Spain? On their national day in 213 (11 Sept), the protest consisted of a human chain across the Catalan coast, called the Via Catalana (<a href="http://via.assemblea.cat/en/catalan-way.html" rel="nofollow">http://via.assemblea.cat/en/catalan-way.html</a>). The year before on the same day, over a million people (!) protested in Barcelona in favour of independence. Yet there seems to be so little mention in the global media.<br />
The president of Catalonia&#8217;s regional government just declared that he would hold a referendum in November. Now is a really interesting time for Catalonia, maybe this year reporters will start taking notice!</p>
			</div>
			<div class="reply"><a class='comment-reply-link' href='/13-most-underreported-news-stories-of-2013/?replytocom=20166#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-20166", "20166", "respond", "19171")'>Reply</a></div><!-- .reply -->
		</div><!-- #comment-##  -->

	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol>
			    
							


